  "theory": {
    "explanation": "Irregular Past Participle forms – Part II\n\nTwo important patterns:\n\nA) Past simple = Past participle (two forms the same):\n  hear  → heard → heard     pay  → paid → paid\n  lose  → lost  → lost      send → sent → sent\n  build → built → built     buy  → bought → bought\n  catch → caught → caught   spend → spent → spent\n\nB) Three different forms:\n  write → wrote → written   speak → spoke → spoken\n  fall  → fell  → fallen    drive → drove → driven\n  break → broke → broken    wear  → wore  → worn\n  choose → chose → chosen   fly   → flew  → flown\n  throw → threw → thrown    eat   → ate   → eaten\n  run   → ran   → run",
    "examples": [
      {
        "sentence": "I haven't written to her in ages.",
        "explanation": "write → wrote → written (three different forms). Past participle = written, not 'wrote'!"
      },
      {
        "sentence": "She's already sent the email.",
        "explanation": "send → sent → sent (past simple = past participle). Both sound the same."
      },
      {
        "sentence": "Have you eaten anything today?",
        "explanation": "eat → ate → eaten (three different forms). Past participle = eaten, not 'ate'!"
      }
    ]
